<includeonly>{{#show:{{{prop|}}}|?Display label|default={{PAGENAME:{{{prop|}}}}}}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Returns a property's display label, falling back to the raw property
name (without `Property:` prefix) if no `Display label` annotation is set.

This is a Tier A primitive — returns a plain string for use in table
headers, form labels, or any custom display markup.

Accepts either a namespaced (`Property:Has_title`) or bare (`Has_title`)
property reference.

Parameter:
* prop - The property page reference

Example:
 {{Property/label|prop=Property:Has_title}}      → "Title"
 {{Property/label|prop=Property:Uncontrolled}}   → "Uncontrolled"  (no Display label set)
</noinclude>
